The core delay pipeline is designed to preserve encoded audio/video packets.
It does not decode or recode the live stream while applying RTMP delay.

Some optional app features can use bundled third-party tools:
- MediaMTX for local RTMP/HLS/WebRTC routing.
- FFmpeg/ffprobe for loading-video conversion and the optional polished Twitch relay.

Those third-party projects keep their own licenses and copyright notices.
